### Description

I found some strange behavior of the types in the form 

```typescript
interface RootForm {
  children: FormGroup<ChildrenForm>;
}

interface ChildrenForm {
  field: FormControl<string>;
}

@Injectable()
class RootService<F extends RootForm> {
  private fb = inject(FormBuilder);

  public form = this.fb.nonNullable.array<FormGroup<F>>([]);
}
```

```shell
TYPESCRIPT ERROR: 
TS2344: Type F does not satisfy the constraint
{ [K in keyof F]: AbstractControl<any, any>; }
Type QuestionForm is not assignable to type
{ [K in keyof F]: AbstractControl<any, any>; }
```

ok, i found a solution to fix this

```typescript
interface RootForm extends Record<string, AbstractControl> {
  children: FormGroup<ChildrenForm>;
}
```

BUT this creates another problem:

```typescript
@Injectable()
class RootService<F extends RootForm> {
  private fb = inject(FormBuilder);

  public form = this.fb.nonNullable.array<FormGroup<F>>([]);

  public childrenForm = computed(() => this.form.at(0).controls.children);
}
```

Type of childrenForm is `AbstractControl<any, any> | FormGroup<ChildrenForm>`, although I just want to see it there `FormGroup<ChildrenForm>`

Of course, the type can be cast, but it is also necessary to take into account that the form can be `undefined`. Plus, if the form is complex and you often have to create such computed, you need to cast the type each time and complicate the code

